CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1955, pg. A8 reads: "NAACP Protest Rally: 3,000 Hear Emmett Till Case Facts; Give; Urge United States to Act - Salutes Speaker - Courier Publisher W. Beverly Carter introduced Dr. Howard as a man who's leading the fight for first class citizenship for negroes in Mississippi."
TitMainTitle: Helen Howard, Rev. LeRoy Patrick, Jessie Vann, W. Beverly Carter, seated on stage, with Bishop Charles H. Foggie, seated on left in background, at Soldier's and Sailor's Memorial Hall for NAACP Protest Rally
